---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Practical Portugal Car Rental Guides | TripAxle"
  description="Handle the practical issues that affect pickup, driving, and day-to-day rental use in Portugal."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Practical Guides</p>
    <h1>Practical Car Rental Guides for Smarter Trips</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Handle the practical side of renting a car in Portugal with more confidence.
      This section focuses on toll roads, transmission choice, fuel, pickup preparation,
      and the real-world details that can affect the rental experience once your trip is underway.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="top-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>What this section covers</h2>
      <p>
        This section focuses on the practical side of renting and driving, not the contract language.
        These guides help with the everyday issues travelers run into before pickup, at pickup, and on the road.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Toll roads, fuel labels, and transmission choice</li>
        <li>Pickup preparation and rental-day logistics</li>
        <li>Common issues that can affect the trip in real life</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Practical guides</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/portugal-toll-roads-for-rental-cars">Portugal toll roads for rental cars</a></li>
        <li>Can you rent a car in Portugal with a debit card?</li>
        <li>Manual vs automatic rental cars in Portugal</li>
        <li>What to photograph when picking up a rental car</li>
        <li>What happens if your flight is late for car rental pickup?</li>
        <li>After-hours car rental returns in Portugal</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="content-grid">
    <article class="main-card">
      <h2>What these guides will help with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Understanding practical issues before you drive away</li>
        <li>Knowing what to check before pickup and before fuel stops</li>
        <li>Handling common friction points during the rental itself</li>
        <li>Making day-to-day rental use feel simpler and less stressful</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to use this hub</h2>
      <p>
        Start here if you already understand the basic booking terms and want help with the practical side of renting.
        These guides are meant to support the real-world part of the trip: pickup, driving, tolls, fuel, and the smaller
        details that can cause stress if you do not plan for them.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you still need help comparing insurance, deposits, holds, or rental terms before reserving,
        go back to Booking Basics. If your questions are specific to arrival logistics, use the airport rental guides.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="side-card">
      <h2>Related Portugal pages</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/portugal-guide">Portugal Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/airport-rental-guides">Airport Rental Guides</a></li>
        <li><a href="/booking-basics">Booking Basics</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <style>
    .hero {
      padding: 2rem 0 2.25rem;
      max-width: 760px;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      color: #2f6fed;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
      line-height: 1.08;
    }

    .intro {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      color: #5b5b55;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      max-width: 680px;
    }

    .top-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .content-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .card,
    .main-card,
    .side-card {
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid #e4e4de;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
    }

    li + li {
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }

    .side-card a {
      color: #2f6fed;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .top-grid,
      .content-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
